Business Model Canvas: Alonso Web Studio

1. Value Propositions

What value do we deliver to the customer?

•
Speed & Efficiency: A professional, live website in 7 days, not months.

•
Stress Reduction: "Zero code, zero headache" service that handles all technical complexity.

•
Professionalism: High-end design that builds credibility and pride (solving the "embarrassment" pain point).

•
Growth Automation: Built-in tools like AI chatbots and SEO to generate leads while the owner sleeps.

•
Affordability: Competitive pricing ($1k-$5k or $15-$50/mo) accessible to small businesses.

2. Customer Segments

For whom are we creating value?

•
Primary Avatar: "David Chen" – The Problem-Aware Small Business Owner.

•
Demographics: 35-55 years old, service-based businesses (consultants, trades, local retail), $100k-$500k annual revenue.

•
Psychographics: Overwhelmed, time-poor, tech-skeptical but results-oriented, values trust and personal relationships.

3. Channels

How do we reach our customer segments?

•
Direct Sales: Local networking, chamber of commerce meetings (leveraging the "Alonso" personal brand).

•
Referrals: Incentivized word-of-mouth from satisfied clients.

•
Content Marketing: LinkedIn posts sharing "before/after" case studies and simple tech tips.

•
Website: The Alonso Web Studio platform itself (SEO-optimized).

4. Customer Relationships

What type of relationship does each customer segment expect?

•
Personal & Trusted: High-touch onboarding (the "Vibe Code" intake) to build rapport.

•
Reliable Partner: Ongoing support via the monthly subscription model (not a "ghosting" freelancer).

•
Automated Efficiency: Self-service updates and reports for the "Growth Partner" tier.

5. Revenue Streams

For what value are our customers really willing to pay?

•
One-Time Build Fees: $1,000 - $5,000 for initial website design and launch.

•
Recurring Subscriptions: $15 - $50/month for hosting, maintenance, AI chatbot, and SEO monitoring.

•
Add-On Services: Future potential for copywriting, advanced automation, or social media management.

6. Key Resources

What key resources do our value propositions require?

•
The "Alonso" Brand: Your reputation and personal network.

•
AI Tech Stack: The tools used to generate sites quickly (React, Tailwind, AI content generators).

•
The Platform: The "Alonso Web Studio" website and intake system.

•
Templates: A library of high-quality, industry-specific designs.

7. Key Activities

What key activities do our value propositions require?

•
Client Acquisition: Networking and sales calls.

•
"Vibe Coding": Rapidly customizing templates using AI based on client intake.

•
Quality Assurance: Reviewing AI outputs to ensure professional standards.

•
Customer Support: Responding to client update requests and maintaining site uptime.

8. Key Partnerships

Who are our key partners?

•
Technology Providers: Hosting platforms (Vercel/Netlify), AI API providers (OpenAI), Payment processors (Stripe).

•
Complementary Service Providers: Local graphic designers or photographers to refer work to (and get referrals from).

9. Cost Structure

What are the most important costs inherent in our business model?

•
Software Subscriptions: Hosting, AI tools, domain management.

•
Time: Your personal time spent on sales and development (initially the biggest cost).

•
Marketing: Local event fees, business cards, potentially paid ads later.

